Rating: 4
Loved this recipe! For the syrup, I doubled the lemon juice and zest. I did not have honey, so sustituted pure maple syrup and used turbinado raw cane sugar which gave it a little molasses flavor...YUM! This is a keeper...

Rating: 3
This is a great recipe - very quick and easy to put together from ingredients in your pantry, and no cleanup required either! I increased the amount of lemon juice in the syrup to 3 teaspoons, and also added some dark rum along with the zest. Next time I might add a wee bit more flour so that the cake is a little less sticky after having soaked in the syrup.

Rating: 4
I doubled the recipe because there was two of us. I was looking for something quick and easy to make because I had to prepare a birthday dinner in a very short time. This was perfect. Would have been too sweet if not for the lemon, which balances the sweetness well. Definitely a keeper for me.

